</taxonomicName>
provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFB2FFBAEB001127FEAE536A" author="Anderson, S." box="[109,292,1337,1362]" pageId="50" pageNumber="50" pagination="1 - 652" refId="ref32736" refString="Anderson, S. 1997. Mammals of Bolivia: taxonomy and distribution. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 231: 1 - 652." type="journal article" year="1997">Anderson (1997)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFB2FFBAEA5D1124FD8B536A" author="Patton, J. L. &amp; M. N. F. da Silva &amp; J. R. Malcolm" box="[304,513,1337,1362]" pageId="50" pageNumber="50" pagination="1 - 306" refId="ref41060" refString="Patton, J. L., M. N. F. da Silva, and J. R. Malcolm. 2000. Mammals of the Rio Jurua and the evolutionary and ecological diversification of Amazonia. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 244: 1 - 306." type="journal article" year="2000">Patton et al. (2000)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFB2FFBAE9631124FF38534C" author="Voss, R. S. &amp; D. P. Lunde &amp; N. B. Simmons" pageId="50" pageNumber="50" pagination="1 - 236" refId="ref43927" refString="Voss, R. S., D. P. Lunde, and N. B. Simmons. 2001. The mammals of Paracou, French Guiana: a neotropical lowland rainforest fauna Part 2. Nonvolant species. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 263: 1 - 236." type="journal article" year="2001">Voss et al. (2001)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFB2FFBAEBAD1142FE26534C" author="Carleton, M. D. &amp; L. H. Emmons &amp; G. G. Musser" box="[192,428,1372,1396]" pageId="50" pageNumber="50" pagination="1 - 32" refId="ref33761" refString="Carleton, M. D., L. H. Emmons, and G. G. Musser. 2009. A new species of the rodent genus Oecomys (Cricetidae: Sigmodontinae: Oryzomyini) from eastern Bolivia, with emended definitions of O. concolor (Wagner) and O. mamorae (Thomas). American Museum Novitates 3661: 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="2009">Carleton et al. (2009)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFB2FFBAEAD61142FF3853AE" author="Hice, C. L. &amp; P. M. Velazco" pageId="50" pageNumber="50" pagination="1 - 135" refId="ref37128" refString="Hice, C. L., and P. M. Velazco. 2012. The non-volant mammals of the Reserva Nacional Allpahuayo-Mishana, Loreto, Peru. Special Publications, Texas Tech University Museum 60: 1 - 135." type="journal article" year="2012">Hice and Velazco (2012)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFB2FFBAEBAD1160FE7C53AE" author="Carleton, M. D. &amp; G. G. Musser" box="[192,502,1406,1430]" pageId="50" pageNumber="50" pagination="393 - 417" refId="ref33694" refString="Carleton, M. D., and G. G. Musser. 2015. Genus Oecomys Thomas, 1906. In J. L. Patton, U. F. J. Pardinas, and G. D'Elia (editors), Mammals of South America, vol. 2: Rodents: 393 - 417. Chicago: University of Chicago Press." type="book chapter" year="2015">Carleton and Musser (2015)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFB2FFBAE9681160FE855380" author="Ruelas, D. &amp; U. F. J. Pardinas" pageId="50" pageNumber="50" pagination="419" refId="ref41933" refString="Ruelas, D., and U. F. J. Pardinas. 2017. White-bellied arboreal rice rat Oecomys bicolor. In D. E. Wilson, T. E. Lacher, Jr., and R. A. Mittermeier (editors), Handbook of the mammals of the world: 419. Barcelona: Lynx Edicions." type="book chapter" year="2017">Ruelas and Pardiñas (2017)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFB2FFBAEA2911BEFDD95380" author="Suarez-Villota, E. Y. &amp; A. P. Carmignotto &amp; M. V. Brandao &amp; A. R. Percequillo &amp; J. Silva" box="[324,595,1440,1464]" pageId="50" pageNumber="50" pagination="182 - 210" refId="ref42658" refString="Suarez-Villota, E. Y., A. P. Carmignotto, M. V. Brandao, A. R. Percequillo, and M. J. d. J. Silva. 2018. Systematics of the genus Oecomys (Sigmodontinae: Oryzomyini): molecular phylogenetic, cytogenetic and morphological approaches reveal cryptic species. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 184: 182 - 210." type="journal article" year="2018">Suárez-Villota et al. (2018)</bibRefCitation>
. No subspecies are currently recognized in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D1BFFB2FFBAE97E11DCFDF653E2" baseAuthorityName="Tomes" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[531,636,1474,1498]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Oecomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="50" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis id="B90EEA8AFFB2FFBAE97E11DCFDF653E2" box="[531,636,1474,1498]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="50">O. bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFB2FFBAEB1E11FAFE1F53C4" author="Carleton, M. D. &amp; G. G. Musser" box="[115,405,1508,1532]" pageId="50" pageNumber="50" pagination="393 - 417" refId="ref33694" refString="Carleton, M. D., and G. G. Musser. 2015. Genus Oecomys Thomas, 1906. In J. L. Patton, U. F. J. Pardinas, and G. D'Elia (editors), Mammals of South America, vol. 2: Rodents: 393 - 417. Chicago: University of Chicago Press." type="book chapter" year="2015">Carleton and Musser, 2015</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFB2FFBAEACD11FAFF285026" author="Ruelas, D. &amp; U. F. J. Pardinas" pageId="50" pageNumber="50" pagination="419" refId="ref41933" refString="Ruelas, D., and U. F. J. Pardinas. 2017. White-bellied arboreal rice rat Oecomys bicolor. In D. E. Wilson, T. E. Lacher, Jr., and R. A. Mittermeier (editors), Handbook of the mammals of the world: 419. Barcelona: Lynx Edicions." type="book chapter" year="2017">Ruelas and Pardiñas, 2017</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D1BFFB2FFBAEBDE1219FED05026" baseAuthorityName="Tomes" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[179,346,1542,1566]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Oecomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="50" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis id="B90EEA8AFFB2FFBAEBDE1219FED05026" box="[179,346,1542,1566]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="50">Oecomys bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from other congeneric species by the following combination of characteristics: dorsal fur ranging from orange brown to rufous brown; ventral pelage uniformly white; tail (105%–112% of head-body length) unicolored with a moderately penciled tip; skull robust, with short rostrum, narrow interorbit with finely beaded supraorbital ledges, and relatively inflated braincase; zygomatic arches slightly narrower rostrally and divergent toward braincase; bony palate with a pair of prominent posterolateral palatal pits; carotid circulatory pattern complete (sphenofrontal foramen and squamosoalisphenoid groove present, stapedial foramen small but present); and ectotympanic bullae small, exposing much of medial periotic (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFB2FFBAE8E811A2FB3253EC" author="Carleton, M. D. &amp; G. G. Musser" box="[901,1208,1468,1492]" pageId="50" pageNumber="50" pagination="393 - 417" refId="ref33694" refString="Carleton, M. D., and G. G. Musser. 2015. Genus Oecomys Thomas, 1906. In J. L. Patton, U. F. J. Pardinas, and G. D'Elia (editors), Mammals of South America, vol. 2: Rodents: 393 - 417. Chicago: University of Chicago Press." type="book chapter" year="2015">Carleton and Musser, 2015</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFB2FFBAE9C111C1FC4753CF" author="Ruelas, D. &amp; U. F. J. Pardinas" box="[684,973,1503,1527]" pageId="50" pageNumber="50" pagination="419" refId="ref41933" refString="Ruelas, D., and U. F. J. Pardinas. 2017. White-bellied arboreal rice rat Oecomys bicolor. In D. E. Wilson, T. E. Lacher, Jr., and R. A. Mittermeier (editors), Handbook of the mammals of the world: 419. Barcelona: Lynx Edicions." type="book chapter" year="2017">Ruelas and Pardiñas, 2017</bibRefCitation>
). Our specimens conform to previous descriptions of the species, and their measurements fall within the range of size variation previously documented.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
